TOLLYWOOD : FLASH NEWSFire Accident At Baahubali Sets, 4 InjuredBaahubali's shooting hit by fire mishapDirector Rajamouli's magnum opus Baahubali's shooting is progressing at brisk pace in Ramoji Film City, Hyderabad. The film's shooting was hit by a mishap on Saturday evening. While the filmmakers were shooting war scenes on the crew in RFC, fire accident occurred and four fighters suffered minor burns.This resulted in fire. Four fighters who were waiting for their chance to participate in fire scenes were standing next to the equipment and caught fire. Fighters Santosh, Paandu, Ganesh and Santosh suffered minor injuries and received first aid in a private hospital in Hayath Nagar.Film stars Prabhas, Rana, Anushka and Tamannaah in lead roles. M.M.Keeravani is the music director for the film produced by Arka Media Works banner.
